sdom%20Ventures%2C%20headed%20by%20Bradley%20Horowitz%2C%20wrote%20early%20checks%20to%20OpenAI%20in%202023%20and%20to%20Anthropic%20in%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHorowitz%20became%20a%20full-time%20VC%20after%20serving%20as%20Google's%20VP%20of%20product%20for%2015%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHorowitz%20took%20the%20fifth%20spot%20on%20Business%20Insider's%202026%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseed-100-best-early-stage-vc-investors-2026-5%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESeed%20100%20list.%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20OpenAI%20and%20Anthropic%20both%20race%20toward%20blockbuster%20IPOs%2C%20there%20are%20not%20many%20investors%20who%20can%20claim%20the%20distinction%20of%20backing%20both%20companies%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBradley%20Horowitz%2C%20through%20his%20venture%20firm%2C%20Wisdom%20Ventures%2C%20wrote%20early%20checks%20to%20OpenAI%20in%202023%20and%20to%20Anthropic%20in%202024.%20He%20was%20also%20an%20angel%20investor%20in%20Cerebras%2C%20which%20soared%20in%20its%20public%20market%20debut%20last%20week.%20His%20other%20seed%20investments%20include%20Slack%2C%20Miro%2C%20Ramp%2C%20and%20ScaleAI%2C%20a%20remarkable%20track%20record%20that%20has%20made%20Horowitz%20a%20perennial%20top%20VC%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseed-100-best-early-stage-vc-investors-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20Seed%20100.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bradley%20Horowitz%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fe2d55e1443b8dc48e35c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECarolyn%20Fong%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%2015%20years%20as%20a%20Google%20product%20executive%20helping%20build%20the%20very%20tools%20that%20define%20our%20digital%20lives%E2%80%94from%20Gmail%20to%20Google%20Photos%E2%80%94%20Horowitz%20now%20wants%20to%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Btech-enabled%20well-being%2C%26quot%3B%20seeking%20out%20founders%20who%20can%20use%20technology%20to%20reduce%20screen%20time%20and%20foster%20genuine%2C%20real-world%20human%20connection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20it%20was%20while%20working%20on%20Google%20Photos%20a%20decade%20ago%20that%20he%20realized%20machine%20learning%20was%20advancing%20rapidly%2C%20when%20it%20could%20accurately%20identify%20objects%20in%20photos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20able%20to%20do%20automatic%20image%20recognition%2C%20so%20you%20no%20longer%20needed%20tagging%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20remembers.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20worked%20on%20that%20problem%20for%2020%20years%2C%20so%20to%20see%20it%20finally%20starting%20to%20work%20was%20a%20leading%20indicator%20that%20there%20were%20some%20fundamental%20changes%20coming.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHorowitz%20had%20known%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20since%20he%20was%20a%20young%20founder%20in%20Y%20Combinator%20at%20his%20previous%20company%2C%20Loopt.%20They%20stayed%20in%20touch%2C%20and%20when%20Wisdom%20Ventures%20was%20investing%20its%20first%20fund%2C%20Horowitz%20and%20his%20partners%20called%20Altman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bradley%20Horowitz%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fe2c8dba7ef34b41f36822%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223917%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECarolyn%20Fong%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWisdom%20also%20backed%20Anthropic%20the%20next%20year%2C%20bucking%20the%20conventional%20Silicon%20Valley%20prohibition%20against%20backing%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20picking%20a%20winner%20in%20this%20race%2C%26quot%3B%20Horowitz%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20humanity%20to%20be%20the%20winner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2257a2d9b8-bba9-430e-bcf9-812821ea97a0%5C%22%3EThe%20flat%20tire%20test%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20evaluating%20founders%2C%20Horowitz%20tries%20to%20understand%20how%20they%20would%20act%20when%20things%20go%20wrong%2C%20which%20he%20calls%20the%20%26quot%3Bflat%20tire%20test.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20go%20on%20a%20road%20trip%20with%20a%20group%20of%20people%20and%20you%20get%20a%20flat%20tire%20three%20miles%20into%20it%2C%20some%20people%20are%20Debbie%20Downers%20and%20bummed%20out%20at%20your%20bad%20luck%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20while%20others%20roll%20up%20their%20sleeves%20and%20make%20the%20best%20of%20a%20bad%20situation.%20%26quot%3BI%20find%20it%20more%20fun%20to%20work%20with%20the%20latter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225514%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bradley%20Horowitz%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fe2d94e1443b8dc48e35c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223676%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECarolyn%20Fong%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHorowitz%20gravitates%20toward%20founders%20who%20have%20worked%20in%20a%20bustling%20kitchen%20or%20as%20a%20camp%20counselor%2C%20environments%20where%20things%20break%2C%20stress%20runs%20high%2C%20and%20decisions%20matter%20in%20real%20time.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20some%20people%20who%20crumble%20under%20chaos%2C%20and%20there%20are%20other%20people%20who%20thrive%20under%20chaos%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20drama%20that%20happens%20in%20a%20restaurant%20is%20really%20good%20training%20for%20what%20it%20means%20to%20ship%20a%20product.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20decades%20at%20Google%20and%20backing%20multiple%20breakout%20startups%2C%20Horowitz%20could%20more%20than%20afford%20to%20enjoy%20a%20comfortable%20retirement.%20Instead%2C%20Wisdom%20Ventures%20just%20closed%20an%20oversubscribed%20Fund%20II%20of%20around%20%2480%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225588%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bradley%20Horowitz%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fe2dbec9dd4cb81